The Act requires the Government, as soon as practicable after the Act’s commencement, to constitute a Minimum Wages Board composed of:

* a Chairperson;  
* one member to represent employers;  
* one member to represent workers;  
* one member to represent the employers connected with the industry or trade concerned; and  
* one member to represent the workers engaged in that industry or trade【Sindh Minimum Wages Act 2015, s. 3, p. 5】.

The Chairperson and all members are appointed by the Government【Sindh Minimum Wages Act 2015, s. 3, p. 5】, with the Chairperson required to have adequate knowledge of industrial, labour and economic conditions and to be unaffiliated with any employer or workers’ organization【Sindh Minimum Wages Act 2015, s. 3, p. 5】. The employer‑ and worker‑representative members are appointed after considering nominations, if any, from organisations that the Government deems representative of those constituencies【Sindh Minimum Wages Act 2015, s. 3, p. 5】.
